Class GUI

  • java.lang.Object
    • GUI
  • public class GUI
extends java.lang.Object
    Front-End menu that users interact with to select certain functions that include; creating a Binary Search Tree, browsing through the tree, finding nodes within the tree, inserting additional nodes. This class also uses the ActionListener class that reads the pressing of buttons, to allow users to manouver through the GUI.
    Since:
    2021 - 08 - 06

      • browseTree

        public javax.swing.JFrame browseTree()
        After inputting the BinarySearchTree, textArea is filled with the database and is displayed in the browseFrame.
        Returns:
        browseFrame is returned to actionPerformed where we make sure that the frame is not repeatedly opened.

      • getTree

        public void getTree()
        Creates a new createTreeFrame JFrame that asks the user to input a database that holds the Binary Search Tree. Once input, user has now loaded the database into the BinarySearchTree.

      • insertButton

        public void insertButton()
        Creates a insertFrame JFrame that requires the user to input the student's id, faculty, major and year of study. This then creates a new Node within the BinarySearchTree, which is updated by refreshing the browseFrame.
